intro: Delissea waianaeensis, commonly known as the Hawaiian sea hibiscus, is a flowering plant native to the island of Oahu in Hawaii. It is a member of the Malvaceae family and is characterized by its showy, five-petaled flowers that range in color from white to pink. The plant typically grows in coastal areas and thrives in sandy soils with ample sunlight. It has smooth, green leaves and produces small, round fruits that contain seeds. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a rare and endemic species.
